<h3>Intro</h3>

<img src="Tutorial.png" style="max-height:600px;" />
<p>
    <b>Tyche</b> is a game about tactics that are viable <b>despite</b> the harsh mistress of lady luck.
    You devise a one-time strategy that attempts to maximize the overall probability of success and minimize the overall turns required to defeat the *Enemy Cards*.
    You'll have a little help along the way. Your *Oracle Bar* narrows down the RNG, giving you a hint of what a card at a position will encounter for its roll during the turn.
</p>
<p>
    A single roll of the dice determines both the abilities that a character activates, and also the attacks that the enemy will levy.
    Drag dice from the *Ability Dice* to the card to enable abilities.
</p>
<p>
    END OF TURN: Once every character has completed its abilities, the next turn begins, starting back at position 1.
</p>

